<div id="review_2576813398" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2576813398" />
    <a title="Anneloup Roncin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/73329890-anneloup-roncin"><img alt="Anneloup Roncin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1509640324p2/73329890.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2576813398?book_show_action=true">Oct 29, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anneloup Roncin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anneloup Roncin" href="/user/show/73329890-anneloup-roncin">Anneloup Roncin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/73329890-anneloup-roncin?shelf=favs">favs</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/73329890-anneloup-roncin?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/73329890-anneloup-roncin?shelf=vamps-and-or-werewolfs">vamps-and-or-werewolfs</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/73329890-anneloup-roncin?shelf=superpowers">superpowers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/73329890-anneloup-roncin?shelf=wizards-and-magicians">wizards-and-magicians</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/73329890-anneloup-roncin?shelf=m-m">m-m</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2576813398" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13414299526479116683">Backstories can be everything. Tony Foster and his dear vampire Henry already have a past, and their present evolves arount it. I want to learn more about this past, as I want to read more about their present and futur. <br/><br/>The complexity and rush of the television business is depicted with what I imagine to be an interesting accuracy. <br/>Tanya Huff mokes herself in multiple occasions, in a sarcastic humor about writers. She uses the set of a detective vampire tv show and makes fun of it, when her own </span>
  <span id="freeText13414299526479116683" style="display:none">Backstories can be everything. Tony Foster and his dear vampire Henry already have a past, and their present evolves arount it. I want to learn more about this past, as I want to read more about their present and futur. <br /><br />The complexity and rush of the television business is depicted with what I imagine to be an interesting accuracy. <br />Tanya Huff mokes herself in multiple occasions, in a sarcastic humor about writers. She uses the set of a detective vampire tv show and makes fun of it, when her own vampire used to be one. She mokes dramatic romances more times than not, but writes one all the same. <br />It could have been over the top - a vampire, wizards, another world, with a weird mommy in his memories... But there is just the right amount of humor to make it right. <br /><br />Tony Foster does not take himself too seriously. He is ambitious but not for power, or money. He fights for what is good just because he wants to, when he should be the last person in the room rushing in those kind of situations. And yet he's quick witted enough to defeat shadows and wizards. His own powers are far from the best of him - yet, at least.<br />He is not self indulgent, has a rare quality of looking at others right in the eyes and prevents from judging what he finds. <br /><br />I'll look forward to the following, and advice this book to all who love romances and vampires that do not involve sparkly teenagers with a death wish. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13414299526479116683" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


