<div id="review_2138320990" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2138320990" />
    <a title="Freyavenlyo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20260466-freyavenlyo"><img alt="Freyavenlyo" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1496448275p2/20260466.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2138320990?book_show_action=true">Oct 02, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Freyavenlyo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Freyavenlyo" href="/user/show/20260466-freyavenlyo">Freyavenlyo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781841494760" href="/book/show/607137.Smoke_and_Shadows">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20260466-freyavenlyo?shelf=in-my-library">in-my-library</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20260466-freyavenlyo?shelf=urban-fantasy">urban-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20260466-freyavenlyo?shelf=crime">crime</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20260466-freyavenlyo?shelf=mm-romance">mm-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20260466-freyavenlyo?shelf=lgbt">lgbt</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20260466-freyavenlyo?shelf=vampires">vampires</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2138320990" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10876189977461039933">This is more or less a continuation of the Victoria Nelson series, but not with her as the main character, no this time with Tony Foster, former street boy in the center of supernatural incidents.<br/>Tony Foster works as a very lovable geeky gay PA for a straight to syndication television show “Darkest Night”. After leaving Toronto with Henry Fitzroy for the nice city of Vancouver, the now 24 year old wants to make his way in television and wants to stay as far away from any supernatural trouble as </span>
  <span id="freeText10876189977461039933" style="display:none">This is more or less a continuation of the Victoria Nelson series, but not with her as the main character, no this time with Tony Foster, former street boy in the center of supernatural incidents.<br />Tony Foster works as a very lovable geeky gay PA for a straight to syndication television show “Darkest Night”. After leaving Toronto with Henry Fitzroy for the nice city of Vancouver, the now 24 year old wants to make his way in television and wants to stay as far away from any supernatural trouble as possible.<br /><br />Well, things don’t work out so well.<br /><br />I’ve read Victoria Nelson years ago, so I pretty much forgot everything, or confused things with “Blood Ties”, the TV show based on the Victoria Nelson books. Where there is no Tony. Which is really sad. But being that I watched the TV show equally a long time ago … well, you can guess what happened.<br /><br />So I pretty much started with no background knowledge for this series, only a few stray thoughts that where more confusing than helpful. But I got right into it. The story is really captivating, neither too easy nor too hard to read and follow, very funny at times and very geeky. <br />The characters were all very likable and lovable. Tony is just so cute in my mind. I just want to hug and snuggle him. Henry on the other hand ... let's say, sleep or even a bed need not be involved.<br /><br />Arra was a little bit harder to get to like, but with her situation I knew where she was coming from.<br /><br />All in all it reminded me a little of the Dresden Files by Jim Butcher getting mixed up with the Buffy cast - a very enjoyable read. It’s a really feel-good book. So I’m pretty sure I’ll come back to it again in the future.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10876189977461039933" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


