<div id="review_4013893694" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4013893694" />
    <a title="Jean Nolan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/71855158-jean-nolan"><img alt="Jean Nolan" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4013893694?book_show_action=true">May 21, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jean Nolan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jean Nolan" href="/user/show/71855158-jean-nolan">Jean Nolan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4013893694" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4104519384202364227">I was always in love with Henry. (Isn’t everyone?!?). But... To watch the evolution of Tony’s and the Prince of Darkness’s relationship has been an unmixed pleasure. While I greatly enjoyed the Blood series, I found the Smoke books to be far more fun. <br/>The writing is excellent, the characters, including the secondary characters, dynamic, well-developed, and capable of change, the dialogue and italicized subtext kept me laughing out loud, and the series immediately gained my comfort reread status.</span>
  <span id="freeText4104519384202364227" style="display:none">I was always in love with Henry. (Isn’t everyone?!?). But... To watch the evolution of Tony’s and the Prince of Darkness’s relationship has been an unmixed pleasure. While I greatly enjoyed the Blood series, I found the Smoke books to be far more fun. <br />The writing is excellent, the characters, including the secondary characters, dynamic, well-developed, and capable of change, the dialogue and italicized subtext kept me laughing out loud, and the series immediately gained my comfort reread status.<br />The paranormal aspects of the stories, rather than being clumsily “explained,” are presented in such fashion that the reader’s acceptance is assumed and assured. Sex, while a constant undercurrent, is matter of fact, and not particularly graphic, but - effective.<br />At the risk of dating myself, (old! LOL!), these books are reminiscent of Fritz Leiber’s Fafhrd and the Gray Mouser stories, dealing with human emotion and response perfectly realistically while pushing the boundaries of the (un)natural world deliciously out of shape.<br />Thank you, Tanya Huff!</span>
  <a data-text-id="4104519384202364227" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


